    "As for RSMI, though its index construction time is significantly higher than that of other indexes (9124× larger than ZMI on dataset Lognormal, see Table 4), the trained model is generally more compact for storage and not sensitive to the size of various datasets (about 20MB for all datasets).",
    "Thus, an ideal use case of RSMI is to perform offline training using machines equipped with powerful GPUs and deploy the trained models for subsequent query processing.",
    "All evaluated learned indexes achieve a much more compact structure compared to conventional indexes with a sacrifice of affordable index construction cost.",
